ingredients: {'quantity': '1 ¼', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'graham cracker crumbs'}, {'quantity': '6', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'butter, melted'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'white sugar'}, {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'cold water'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'white sugar'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(.25 ounce) package', 'name': 'unflavored gelatin'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sour cream'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(8 ounce) container', 'name': 'blueberry-flavored yogurt'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'heavy whipping cream'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'blueberries'}
steps: Mix graham cracker crumbs, melted butter, and 1/4 cup white sugar in a bowl. Measure 1/4 cup crust mixture and set aside. Press remaining crust mixture into a 10x6x2-inch pan.. Combine water, 1/2 cup white sugar, and gelatin in a saucepan over medium-low heat; cook and stir until gelatin and sugar dissolve, about 5 minutes.. Stir sour cream and yogurt together in a bowl. Gradually stir gelatin mixture into sour cream mixture; stir in vanilla extract. Refrigerate until partially set, about 30 minutes.. Beat heavy cream in a glass or metal bowl until soft peaks form. Fold sour cream mixture into whipped cream; stir in blueberries. Spread blueberry cream evenly over crust; sprinkle reserved 1/4 graham cracker mixture over dessert. Chill in refrigerator, 8 hours to overnight.

name: Bing Cherry Salad
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(20 ounce) can', 'name': 'crushed pineapple with juice'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(15 ounce) can', 'name': 'pitted Bing cherries in water'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(3 ounce) package', 'name': 'cream cheese, cut into pieces'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(12 fluid ounce) can or bottle', 'name': 'cola-flavored carbonated beverage, or as needed.'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(3 ounce) package', 'name': 'cherry Jell-O®'}
steps: Drain the pineapple juice and cherry water into a 2-cup measuring cup. Pour enough color to make 2 cups; discard the remaining soda. Pour the cola mixture into a saucepan.. Bring the cola mixture to a boil over medium-high heat. Remove from heat, then stir in the pineapple, cherries, cream cheese, and cherry gelatin until gelatin dissolves, about 5 minutes. Pour mixture into a mold or glass baking dish. Refrigerate until set, about 3 hours.

name: Mandarin Orange Gelatin Salad
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(12 ounce) container', 'name': 'frozen whipped topping, thawed'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(11 ounce) can', 'name': 'mandarin oranges, drained'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '(16 ounce) packages', 'name': 'cottage cheese'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(6 ounce) package', 'name': 'orange flavored Jell-O® mix'}
steps: In a large bowl, blend the thawed frozen whipped topping, mandarin oranges, cottage cheese and orange flavored gelatin mix. Chill in the refrigerator 2 to 3 hours before serving.

name: Blueberry Gelatin Salad
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '(3 ounce) packages', 'name': 'grape flavored Jell-O® mix'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'boiling water'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(8 ounce) can', 'name': 'crushed pineapple, undrained'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(21 ounce) can', 'name': 'blueberry pie filling'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(8 ounce) package', 'name': 'cream cheese, softened'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sour cream'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'white sugar'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}
steps: In a large bowl, mix together gelatin powder, boiling water, pineapple and pie filling. Pour into a mold, or glass baking dish, and refrigerate until set, at least 2 hours.. In a medium bowl, mix together the cream cheese, sour cream, sugar and vanilla until smooth. Spread over the top of the gelatin. If using a mold, unmold the gelatin before applying topping.

name: Bing Cherry Gelatin Mold
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(16.5 ounce) can', 'name': 'pitted Bing cherries, drained, juice reserved'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(12 fluid ounce) can', 'name': 'cola-flavored carbonated beverage'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(6 ounce) package', 'name': 'black cherry flavored Jell-O® mix'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(15.25 ounce) can', 'name': 'crushed pineapple, drained'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped pecans'}
steps: In a saucepan, combine the reserved cherry juice with the cola. Bring to a boil, and stir in the gelatin until dissolved. Remove from the heat, and mix in the drained cherries, drained pineapple, and chopped pecans. Pour mixture into a mold sprayed with non-stick cooking spray, and refrigerate for at least 24 hours before serving.

name: Lemon-Lime Soda Gelatin Salad
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(3 ounce) package', 'name': 'lime flavored Jell-O® mix'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'white sugar'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'boiling water'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(8 ounce) package', 'name': 'cream cheese'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(8 ounce) can', 'name': 'crushed pineapple, with juice'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'lemon-lime flavored carbonated beverage'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped pecans'}
steps: In a large bowl, dissolve the gelatin and sugar in the boiling water. Add the cream cheese and whisk until the melted into small chunks. Add pineapple with juice, soda and nuts and stir until evenly combined. Chill until set.

name: Strawberry Lemonade Marshmallow Jell-O®
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(6 ounce) package', 'name': 'strawberry-flavored gelatin (such as Jell-O®)'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(6 ounce) package', 'name': 'lemon-flavored gelatin (such as Jell-O®)'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'boiling water'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'cold water'}, {'quantity': '6', 'unit': '', 'name': 'fresh strawberries, sliced (Optional)'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'miniature marshmallows (Optional)'}
steps: Mix strawberry-flavored gelatin and lemon-flavored gelatin together in a bowl; pour in the boiling water and stir until gelatin mixture is dissolved, at least 2 minutes. Pour the cold water into the mixture and stir until well combined.. Pour gelatin mixture into a mold or leave in the bowl and refrigerate until partially set, about 1 1/2 hours. Mix strawberries and marshmallows into gelatin mixture. Continue chilling until completely set, about 2 1/2 hours more.

name: Pimento Cheese Jell-O® Salad
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(3 ounce) package', 'name': 'lemon-flavored gelatin mix (such as Jell-O®)'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'boiling water'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(8 ounce) can', 'name': 'crushed pineapple with juice'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'white sugar'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(8 ounce) package', 'name': 'pimento cheese'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(8 ounce) container', 'name': 'frozen whipped topping (such as Cool Whip®), thawed'}
steps: Stir lemon gelatin and boiling water in a bowl until gelatin has dissolved; set aside to cool.. Stir crushed pineapple with juice and sugar together in a small saucepan over medium heat until sugar has dissolved and mixture comes to a simmer. Set pineapple mixture aside to cool.. Transfer cooled gelatin and pineapple mixture to a serving dish or mold; stir pimento cheese into mix until completely combined. Gently fold whipped topping into gelatin mixture. Refrigerate overnight.
